  introLines:
  - Do you have any idea how much my time costs? Wrap this up quickly.
  - Where am I? This looks aggressively underfunded.
  answerWhatHappenedBefore: I was celebrating a massive corporate acquisition over
    an expensive glass of wine. Halfway through the bottle, my throat closed up.
    Next thing I know, I'm standing here.
  answerWhatKindOfLife: A highly profitable one. I looked out for number one, acquired
    assets, and left the weak behind. That's just how the world works.
  answerWhatWasYourJob: I dismantled failing companies, sold off their assets, and
    pocketed the restructuring fees. Brutal? Perhaps. Lucrative? Incredibly.
  answerWhatHappenedClothes: This shirt is bespoke Egyptian cotton. It's immaculate
    because I don't do manual labor. I pay others to get dirty for me.
  answerWhyHaveItem: A tie is part of the uniform for success, and the money? Well,
    I assumed everyone has a price. How much to let me pass through?
